            	def ajax_cage_shelf_stats
          
      224. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    224. 
            
            

            

            		cs = CageShelf.where(id: params[:id]).first
          
      225. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    225. 
            
            

            

            		stats = {}
          
      226. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    226. 
            
            

            

            		if cs.nil?
          
      227. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    227. 
            
            

            

            			stats[:error] = "Could not find cage shelf with ID #{params[:cage_shelf_id]}"
          
      228. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    228. 
            
            

            

            		else
          
      229. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    229. 
            
            

            

            			pos = cs.physical_objects
          
      230. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    230. 
            
            

            

            			stats[:count] = pos.size
          
      231. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    231. 
            
            

            

            			twoK = 0
          
      232. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    232. 
            
            

            

            			fourK = 0
          
      233. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    233. 
            
            

            

            			durationSec = 0
          
      234. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    234. 
            
            

            

            			pos.each do |p|
          
      235. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    235. 
            
            

            

            				p = p.specific
          
      236. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    236. 
            
            

            

            				if !p.current_scan_settings.nil?
          
      237. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    237. 
            
            

            

            					if p.current_scan_settings.scan_resolution == '2k'
          
      238. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    238. 
            
            

            

            						twoK += 1
          
      239. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    239. 
            
            

            

            					end
          
      240. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    240. 
            
            

            

            					if p.current_scan_settings.scan_resolution == '4k'
          
      241. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    241. 
            
            

            

            						fourK += 1
          
      242. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    242. 
            
            

            

            					end
          
      243. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    243. 
            
            

            

            				end
          
      244. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    244. 
            
            

            

            				unless p.footage.blank? || p.gauge.blank?
          
      245. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    245. 
            
            

            

            					durationSec += ((PhysicalObjectsHelper::GAUGES_TO_FRAMES_PER_FOOT[p.gauge] * p.footage) / 24)
          
      246. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    246. 
            
            

            

            				end
          
      247. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    247. 
            
            

            

            			end
          
      248. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    248. 
            
            

            

            			stats[:count_2k] = twoK
          
      249. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    249. 
            
            

            

            			stats[:percent_2k] = (twoK + fourK > 0) ? twoK / (twoK + fourK) : 0
          
      250. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    250. 
            
            

            

            			stats[:count_4k] =  fourK
          
      251. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    251. 
            
            

            

            			stats[:percent_4k] = (twoK + fourK > 0) ? fourK / (twoK + fourK) : 0
          
      252. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    252. 
            
            

            

            			stats[:total_duration] = hh_mm_sec(durationSec)
          
      253. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    253. 
            
            

            

            		end
          
      254. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    254. 
            
            

            

            		render json: stats.to_json
          
      255. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    255. 
            
            

            

            	end
          
      256. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    256. 
            
            

            

            
          
      257.

              def update

              def update_split_title

      356.

                # converts the JavaScript Map object into a Ruby hash { title_id => [array of physical object ids]}. This map contains
          
      357.

                # title ids mapped to the list of physical object ids. If the map key == @title (the title that is being split),
          
      358.

      360.

      361.

      367. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    367. 
            
            

            

                    if @map[t_id].size > 0
          
      368.

      369.

      370.

      375.

      380.

                      if @checked.size > 0

            	def show_mark_found
          
      594. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    594. 
            
            

            

            		@physical_objects = []#PhysicalObject.where_current_workflow_status_is(nil, nil, false, WorkflowStatus::MISSING)
          
      595.

            	end
          
      597. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    597. 
            
            

            

            
          
      598. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    598. 
            
            

            

            	# Rules about adding a PO to a mark found set start with multiple PO having shared titles.
          
      599. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    599. 
            
            

            

            	# 1) the first *Missing* PO is always accepted
          
      600. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    600. 
            
            

            

            	# 2) Subsequent scans are sent with an array of accepted POs so far. The scanned PO (params[:iu_barcode]) is compared
          
      601. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    601. 
            
            

            

            	# to the already scanned barcode (params[:barcodes]) and the 'candidate' is only accepted if it has at least one title
          
      602. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    602. 
            
            

            

            	# in common with the already scanned POs.
          
      603. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    603. 
            
            

            

            	# 3) If the candidate is not missing, doesn't match and existing PO, or does not share at least one title in common with
          
      604. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    604. 
            
            

            

            	# the titles found by POs in params[:barcodes], the resulting JSON returned will contain an error message along with
          
      605. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    605. 
            
            

            

            	# the success attribute set to false
          
      606. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    606. 
            
            

            

            	def ajax_mark_found_lookup
          
      607. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    607. 
            
            

            

            		# the PO that is trying to be added to the set scanned so far
          
      608. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    608. 
            
            

            

            		candidate = PhysicalObject.where(iu_barcode: params[:iu_barcode]).first
          
      609. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    609. 
            
            

            

            		if candidate.nil?
          
      610. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    610. 
            
            

            

            			@error_msg = "Could not find a PhysicalObject with IU Barcode: #{params[:iu_barcode]}"
          
      611. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    611. 
            
            

            

            		elsif candidate.current_location != WorkflowStatus::MISSING
          
      612. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    612. 
            
            

            

            			@error_msg = "PhysicalObject #{params[:iu_barcode]} is not Missing. It's current location is: #{candidate.current_location}"
          
      613. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    613. 
            
            

            

            		else
          
      614. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    614. 
            
            

            

            			# check to see if the passed barcodes have any ids present yet (it's simply a javascript array sent as a string: "[]" is empty)
          
      615. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    615. 
            
            

            

            			bcs = params[:scan_barcodes].tr('\"[]', '').split(',').map(&:to_i)
          
      616. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    616. 
            
            

            

            			if bcs.length > 0
          
      617. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    617. 
            
            

            

            				# turn it into an array of integers
          
      618. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    618. 
            
            

            

            				# lookup the POs in that set
          
      619. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    619. 
            
            

            

            				@pos = PhysicalObject.includes(:titles, :current_workflow_status).where(iu_barcode: bcs)
          
      620. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    620. 
            
            

            

            				# grab the all Titles for those (we've already calculated that there IS an intersection in previous ajax call)
          
      621. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    621. 
            
            

            

            				# and intersect with the candidate's titles/
          
      622. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    622. 
            
            

            

            				@shared_title_ids = @pos.collect{|p| p.titles.collect{|t| t.id}}.flatten.uniq & candidate.titles.collect{|t| t.id}
          
      623. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    623. 
            
            

            

            				# empty array means no intersection
          
      624. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    624. 
            
            

            

            				unless @shared_title_ids.size > 0
          
      625. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    625. 
            
            

            

            					@error_msg = "#{candidate.iu_barcode} does not share any Titles in common with the already select PhysicalObject(s)."
          
      626. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    626. 
            
            

            

            				end
          
      627. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    627. 
            
            

            

            			else
          
      628. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    628. 
            
            

            

            				# This is the first scan so no need to calculate intersections, candidates Titles are the set
          
      629. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    629. 
            
            

            

            				@shared_title_ids = candidate.titles.collect{|t| t.id}
          
      630. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    630. 
            
            

            

            			end
          
      631. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    631. 
            
            

            

            		end
          
      632. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    632. 
            
            

            

            		render json: {:success => @error_msg.nil?, :msg => "#{@error_msg.nil? ? "" : @error_msg}" }.to_json
          
      633. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    633. 
            
            

            

            	end
          
      634. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    634. 
            
            

            

            
          
      635. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    635. 
            
            

            

            	def ajax_load_found_selection_table
          
      636.

            		shared_title_ids = @pos.collect{|p| p.titles.collect{|t| t.id}}.flatten.uniq
          
      639.

            		@titles = Title.where(id: shared_title_ids)

            	def ajax_load_found_cg_table
          
      644. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    644. 
            
            

            

            		ids = params[:ids].tr('\"[]', '').split(',').map(&:to_i)
          
      645. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    645. 
            
            

            

            		@pos = PhysicalObject.where(id: ids)
          
      646. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    646. 
            
            

            

            		@titles = []
          
      647. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    647. 
            
            

            

            		@pos.each do |p|
          
      648. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    648. 
            
            

            

            			if @titles.length == 0
          
      649. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    649. 
            
            

            

            				@titles = p.titles
          
      650. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    650. 
            
            

            

            			else
          
      651. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    651. 
            
            

            

            				@titles = @titles & p.titles
          
      652. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    652. 
            
            

            

            			end
          
      653. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    653. 
            
            

            

            		end
          
      654. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    654. 
            
            

            

            		render partial: 'workflow/mark_found/ajax_load_found_cg_table'
          
      655. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    655. 
            
            

            

            	end
          
      656. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    656. 
            
            

            

            
          
      657.

            	# responds to a barcode scan on the show_mark_found action and allows user to create a new CG and specify a workflow location.
          
      658.

            	def choose_found_workflow
          
      659. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    659. 
            
            

            

            		@physical_object = PhysicalObject.where(iu_barcode: params[:iu_barcode].to_i).first
          
      660. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    660. 
            
            

            

            		if @physical_object.nil?
          
      661. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    661. 
            
            

            

            			@error_msg = "Cannot find a PhysicalObject with IU Barcode: #{params[:iu_barcode]}"
          
      662.

              def initialize(args = {})
          
      127.

                super

                if args.is_a? ActionController::Parameters
          
      129.

                  # !!!! IMPORTANT - how the nested_form gem and active-record_acts_as gem interact with form submission and params.require.permit
          
      130. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    130. 
            
            

            

                  # creates duplicate entries for PhysicalObjectOriginalIdentifiers, PhysicalObjectDates, Languages, RatedConditions, and
          
      131.

                  # BooleanConditions. The above super call ends up ALSO calling the initializer for PhysicalObjects which holds the
          
      132.

                  # actual associations for these objects. They get created correctly. However, I think that when each of these is passed
          
      133.

                  # through self.send() below, this results in a SECOND call to creating that metadata on the underlying physical object.
          
      134.

                  # This only appears to happen during create action on physical objects however, make sure to remove the keys for these

            	def storage_location
          
      169. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    169. 
            
            

            

            		stats = workflow_statuses.where("status_name in (#{WorkflowStatus::STATUS_TYPES_TO_STATUSES['Storage'].map{ |s| "'#{s}'"}.join(',')})").order('created_at ASC')
          
      170. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    170. 
            
            

            

            		# anything with ad_strip > 2.0 must go to the freezer. If it's never been in the freezer if must go to awaiting freezer first for prep.
          
      171. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    171. 
            
            

            

            		# If it was last in the freezer, it should be returned to the freezer. Otherwise, the item is returned to its last storage location,
          
      172. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    172. 
            
            

            

            		# or ingested if it has yet to be put anywhere in storage
          
      173. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    173. 
            
            

            

            		if stats.size > 0
          
      174. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    174. 
            
            

            

            			if self.specific.has_attribute?(:ad_strip) && FREEZER_AD_STRIP_VALS.include?(self.specific.ad_strip)
          
      175. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    175. 
            
            

            

            				(stats.last.status_name == WorkflowStatus::IN_FREEZER ? WorkflowStatus::IN_FREEZER : WorkflowStatus::AWAITING_FREEZER)
          
      176. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    176. 
            
            

            

            			else
          
      177. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    177. 
            
            

            

            				stats.last.status_name
          
      178. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    178. 
            
            

            

            			end
          
      179. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    179. 
            
            

            

            		else
          
      180. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    180. 
            
            

            

            			if self.specific.class == Film && self.specific.ad_strip && FREEZER_AD_STRIP_VALS.include?(self.specific.ad_strip)
          
      181. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    181. 
            
            

            

            				WorkflowStatus::AWAITING_FREEZER
          
      182. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    182. 
            
            

            

            			else
          
      183. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    183. 
            
            

            

            				WorkflowStatus::IN_STORAGE_INGESTED
          
      184. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    184. 
            
            

            

            			end

              def generate_spreadsheet(results)

                  # total JOB completion state: at this point in code, the time taken to run the query AND where we are in spreadsheet

                  # generation. To get that value we have to do some ugly math...
          
      127.

                  #
          
      128.

                  # We defined a guesstimated fixed percentage of a job's runtime for the query portion (because that can't be known

                  # ahead of time): ARBITRARY_QUERY_RUNTIME. The percentage of time a job takes on SS generation is 100 (percent)

      131.

            	# returns a hash containing important information related to the success of the GET. There are 3 different possible

            	# outcomes with different hash contents:

            	def self.pod_group_key_id(mdpi_barcode)
          
      379. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    379. 
            
            

            

            		u = Rails.application.secrets[:pod_service_grouping_url].dup.gsub!(':mdpi_barcode', mdpi_barcode.to_s)
          
      380. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    380. 
            
            

            

            		uri = URI.parse(u)
          
      381. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    381. 
            
            

            

            		http = Net::HTTP.new(uri.host, uri.port)
          
      382. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    382. 
            
            

            

            		http.use_ssl = true
          
      383. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    383. 
            
            

            

            		request = Net::HTTP::Get.new(uri.request_uri)
          
      384. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    384. 
            
            

            

            		request.basic_auth(Rails.application.secrets[:pod_service_username], Rails.application.secrets[:pod_service_password])
          
      385. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    385. 
            
            

            

            		result = http.request(request)
          
      386. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    386. 
            
            

            

            		code = result.code.to_i
          
      387. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    387. 
            
            

            

            		if code == 200
          
      388. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    388. 
            
            

            

            			body = result.body
          
      389. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    389.

            			raise "Missing Group Identifier: #{result}" if gr.nil?

    392. 
            
            

            

            		else
          
      393.

      98. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    98. 
            
            

            

                        @spreadsheet.update_attributes(successful_upload: true)
          
      99. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    99. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      100. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    100. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      101. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    101. 
            
            

            

                  rescue Exception => error
          
      102. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    102. 
            
            

            

                    unless error.class == ManualRollBackError
          
      103. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    103. 
            
            

            

                      @em = error.message << "<br/>"
          
      104. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    104. 
            
            

            

                      error.backtrace.each do |line|
          
      105. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    105. 
            
            

            

                        @em << line << "<br/>"
          
      106. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    106. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      107. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    107. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      108. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    108. 
            
            

            

                    unless @em.blank?
          
      109. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    109. 
            
            

            

                      error_msg << @em.html_safe
          
      110. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    110. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      111. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    111. 
            
            

            

                    @spreadsheet_submission.update_attributes(failure_message: error_msg, successful_submission: false, submission_progress: 100)
          
      112. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    112. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      113. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    113. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      114. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    114. 
            
            

            

              end

              private

              def parse_headers(row)
          
      118. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    118. 
            
            

            

                @headers = Hash.new
          
      119. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    119. 
            
            

            

                @parse_headers_msg = ''
          
      120. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    120. 
            
            

            

                # read all of the file's column headers
          
      121. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    121. 
            
            

            

                row.each_with_index { |header, i|
          
      122. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    122. 
            
            

            

                  puts "[#{header}, #{i}]"
          
      123. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    123. 
            
            

            

                  if @headers.keys.include?(header)
          
      124. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    124. 
            
            

            

                    @parse_headers_msg << "The header <b>#{header}</b> was duplicated at column #{i}<br/>"
          
      125. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    125. 
            
            

            

                  elsif header.blank?
          
      126. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    126. 
            
            

            

                    @parse_headers_msg << "The header is blank at column #{i}<br/>"
          
      127. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    127. 
            
            

            

                  else
          
      128. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    128. 
            
            

            

                    @headers[header.strip] = i
          
      129. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    129. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      130. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    130. 
            
            

            

                }
          
      131. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    131. 
            
            

            

            
          
      132. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    132. 
            
            

            

            
          
      133. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    133. 
            
            

            

                # examine spreadsheet headers to make sure they conform to vocabulary
          
      134. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    134. 
            
            

            

                @headers.keys.each do |ch|
          
      135. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    135. 
            
            

            

                  if !COLUMN_HEADERS.include?(ch)
          
      136. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    136. 
            
            

            

                    @parse_headers_msg << "#{ch} is not a valid column header"
          
      137. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    137. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      138. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    138. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      139. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    139. 
            
            

            

                # make sure that every header is present in the spreadsheet
          
      140. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    140. 
            
            

            

                COLUMN_HEADERS.each do |h|
          
      141. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    141. 
            
            

            

                  unless @headers.keys.include?(h)
          
      142. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    142. 
            
            

            

                    @parse_headers_msg <<  "The column <b>#{h}</b> is missing from the spreadsheet".html_safe
          
      143. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    143. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      144. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    144. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      145. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    145. 
            
            

            

              end
          
      146. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    146. 
            
            

            

              ControlledVocabulary.physical_object_cv('Video')[:stock].collect{|r| r[0]}
          
      147.

              # utility for formatting a string message about a bad column header

              # def parsed_header_message(ch)

              # this method parses a single row in the spreadsheet trying to reconstitute a physical object - it creates association objects (title, series, etc) as well

              def parse_physical_object(row, i)
          
      154. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    154. 
            
            

            

                puts("Parsing Physical Object at Row: #{i + 1}")
          
      155.

                # read all auto parse fields
          
      156. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    156. 
            
            

            

                po = Film.new(spreadsheet_id: @spreadsheet.id)
          
      157. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    157. 
            
            

            

                HEADERS_TO_ASSIGNER.keys.each do |k|
          
      158. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    158.

      159. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    159. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      160. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    160. 
            
            

            

                # date created
          
      161. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    161. 
            
            

            

                begin
          
      162. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    162. 
            
            

            

                  d = Date.strptime(row[column_index DATE_CREATED], '%Y/%m/%d')
          
      163. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    163. 
            
            

            

                  po.date_inventoried = d
          
      164. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    164. 
            
            

            

                rescue
          
      165.

                  po.errors.add(:date, "Unable to parse date created")
          
      166. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    166. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      167. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    167. 
            
            

            

            
          
      168.

                if !row[column_index EDGE_CODE_DATE].blank?
          
      169. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    169. 
            
            

            

                  edge_codes = row[column_index EDGE_CODE_DATE].split(' ; ')

                  edge_codes.each do |d|
          
      171.

      172. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    172. 
            
            

            

                  end

                end

    174. 
            
            

            

            
          
      175.

                # manually parse the other values to ensure conformance to controlled vocabulary

    176. 
            
            

            

                dur = row[column_index DURATION]
          
      177.

                unless dur.blank?

                  end
          
      183. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    183. 
            
            

            

                end

                dates = row[column_index DATE].to_s
          
      588. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    588. 
            
            

            

                unless dates.blank?
          
      589. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    589. 
            
            

            

                  dates.split(DELIMITER).each do |date|
          
      590. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    590. 
            
            

            

                    # the HEX codes in the middle are for MS Excel which changes '-' (minus) to en dashes and/or em dashes
          
      591. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    591. 
            
            

            

                    date_type_rgx = /^(([\[\]0-9\/\?]+)( ?[-\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x93]{1,1} ?([\[\]0-9\/\?]+))?) ?(\(([a-zA-Z ]+)\))?/
          
      592. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    592. 
            
            

            

                    match = date_type_rgx.match(date)
          
      593. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    593. 
            
            

            

                    if match.nil?
          
      594. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    594. 
            
            

            

                      po.errors.add(:title_date, "Malformed date #{date}")
          
      595. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    595. 
            
            

            

                    else
          
      596. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    596. 
            
            

            

                      date_set = DateHelper.convert_dates(match[1])
          
      597. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    597. 
            
            

            

                      # error case - start date will always be !nil unless the string is malformed.
          
      598. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    598. 
            
            

            

                      # DateHelper.convert_dates will also set :start_date to nil if end_date exists but is malformed
          
      599. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    599. 
            
            

            

                      if date_set[:start_date].nil?
          
      600.

      601. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    601. 
            
            

            

                      else
          
      602. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    602. 
            
            

            

                        type = (match[6].blank? ? 'TBD' : @title_date_types.include?(match[6]) ? match[6] : nil)
          
      603. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    603. 
            
            

            

                        if type.nil?
          
      604. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    604. 
            
            

            

                          po.errors.add(:title_date, "Unknown title date type: #{date}")
          
      605. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    605. 
            
            

            

                        else
          
      606. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    606. 
            
            

            

                          td = TitleDate.new(title_id: title.id, date_text: match[1], date_type: type)

                          title.title_dates << td
          
      608. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    608. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      609. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    609. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      610. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    610. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      611.

              require 'manual_roll_back_error'

              # special logger for parsing spreadsheets

              def self.logger

                @@logger ||= Logger.new("#{Rails.root}/log/spreadsheet_submission_logger.log")

              @@mutex = Mutex.new

              def initialize(csv, spreadsheet, spreadsheet_submission)
          
      39. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    39. 
            
            

            

                @csv = csv
          
      40. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    40. 
            
            

            

                @spreadsheet = spreadsheet
          
      41. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    41. 
            
            

            

                @spreadsheet_submission = spreadsheet_submission
          
      42. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    42. 
            
            

            

                @title_cv = ControlledVocabulary.title_cv
          
      43. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    43. 
            
            

            

                @title_date_cv = ControlledVocabulary.title_date_cv
          
      44. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    44. 
            
            

            

                @title_date_types =  @title_date_cv[:date_type].collect{ |d| d[0] }
          
      45. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    45. 
            
            

            

                @title_genre_cv = ControlledVocabulary.title_genre_cv[:genre].collect { |x| x[0] }
          
      46. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    46. 
            
            

            

                @title_form_cv = ControlledVocabulary.title_form_cv[:form].collect { |x| x[0] }
          
      47. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    47. 
            
            

            

              end
          
      48. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    48. 
            
            

            

            
          
      49. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    49. 
            
            

            

              def parse_csv
          
      50. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    50. 
            
            

            

                parse_headers(@csv[0])
          
      51. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    51. 
            
            

            

                if @parse_headers_msg.size > 0
          
      52. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    52. 
            
            

            

                  @spreadsheet_submission.update_attributes(failure_message: @parse_headers_msg, successful_submission: false, submission_progress: 100)
          
      53. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    53. 
            
            

            

                else
          
      54. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    54. 
            
            

            

                  @cv = ControlledVocabulary.physical_object_cv('RecordedSound')
          
      55. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    55. 
            
            

            

                  @l_cv = ControlledVocabulary.language_cv
          
      56. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    56. 
            
            

            

                  # the error message that gets stored in the SpreadSheetSubmission if it fails parsing
          
      57. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    57. 
            
            

            

                  error_msg = ""
          
      58. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    58. 
            
            

            

                  # all physical objects created from the spreadsheet
          
      59. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    59. 
            
            

            

                  all_physical_objects = []
          
      60. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    60. 
            
            

            

                  begin
          
      61. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    61. 
            
            

            

                    PhysicalObject.transaction do
          
      62. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    62. 
            
            

            

                      # parsing spreadsheets is a two pass process. First pass makes sure that values in cells conform to the specification
          
      63. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    63. 
            
            

            

                      # marking each row as bad with a custom error message in the physical object if something erroneous is found. Since
          
      64. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    64. 
            
            

            

                      # ActiveRecord validation clears the errors map, we need to make this first pass before we attempt to save any records.
          
      65. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    65. 
            
            

            

                      # Only if all records pass this initial "validation" can we move on to actually attempting to persist
          
      66. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    66. 
            
            

            

                      # the Physical Objects in the database. We call save (instead of save!) to avoid the exception that would roll back
          
      67. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    67. 
            
            

            

                      # the whole transaction - so that we can process all physical objects to determine all rows that failed rather than
          
      68. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    68. 
            
            

            

                      # just the first row.
          
      69. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    69. 
            
            

            

                      @csv.each_with_index do |row, i|
          
      70. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    70. 
            
            

            

                        unless i == 0
          
      71. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    71. 
            
            

            

                          po = parse_physical_object(row, i)
          
      72. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    72. 
            
            

            

                          all_physical_objects << po
          
      73. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    73. 
            
            

            

                          if po.errors.any?
          
      74. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    74. 
            
            

            

                            error_msg << gen_error_msg(i, po)
          
      75. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    75. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      76. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    76. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      77. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    77. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      78. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    78. 
            
            

            

            
          
      79. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    79. 
            
            

            

                      # if @error_msg has length > 0 something blew up... otherwise we can pass off to ActiveRecord validation to see
          
      80. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    80. 
            
            

            

                      # passes/fails Rails validation
          
      81. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    81. 
            
            

            

                      if error_msg.nil? || error_msg.length == 0
          
      82. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    82. 
            
            

            

                        all_physical_objects.each_with_index do |po, index|
          
      83. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    83. 
            
            

            

                          unless po.save
          
      84. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    84. 
            
            

            

                            error_msg << gen_error_msg(index + 1, po)
          
      85. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    85. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      86. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    86. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      87. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    87. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      88. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    88. 
            
            

            

                      if error_msg.length > 0
          
      89. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    89. 
            
            

            

                        raise ManualRollBackError
          
      90. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    90. 
            
            

            

                      else
          
      91. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    91. 
            
            

            

                        @spreadsheet_submission.update_attributes(successful_submission: true, submission_progress: 100)
          
      92. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    92. 
            
            

            

                        @spreadsheet.update_attributes(successful_upload: true)
          
      93. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    93. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      94. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    94. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      95. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    95. 
            
            

            

                  rescue Exception => error
          
      96. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    96. 
            
            

            

                    unless error.class == ManualRollBackError
          
      97. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    97. 
            
            

            

                      @em = error.message << "<br/>"
          
      98. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    98. 
            
            

            

                      error.backtrace.each do |line|
          
      99. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    99. 
            
            

            

                        @em << line << "<br/>"
          
      100. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    100. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      101. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    101. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      102. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    102. 
            
            

            

                    unless @em.blank?
          
      103. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    103. 
            
            

            

                      error_msg << @em.html_safe
          
      104. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    104. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      105. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    105. 
            
            

            

                    @spreadsheet_submission.update_attributes(failure_message: error_msg, successful_submission: false, submission_progress: 100)
          
      106. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    106. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      107. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    107. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      108. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    108. 
            
            

            

              end
          
      109. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    109. 
            
            

            

            
          
      110. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    110. 
            
            

            

              private
          
      111. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    111. 
            
            

            

              def parse_headers(row)
          
      112. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    112. 
            
            

            

                @headers = Hash.new
          
      113. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    113. 
            
            

            

                @parse_headers_msg = ''
          
      114. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    114. 
            
            

            

                # read all of the file's column headers
          
      115. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    115. 
            
            

            

                row.each_with_index { |header, i|
          
      116. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    116. 
            
            

            

                  puts "[#{header.strip}, #{i}]"
          
      117. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    117. 
            
            

            

                  if @headers.keys.include?(header.strip)
          
      118. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    118. 
            
            

            

                    @parse_headers_msg << "The header <b>#{header.strip}</b> was duplicated at column #{i}<br/>"
          
      119. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    119. 
            
            

            

                  elsif header.blank?
          
      120. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    120. 
            
            

            

                    @parse_headers_msg << "The header is blank at column #{i}<br/>"
          
      121. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    121. 
            
            

            

                  else
          
      122. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    122. 
            
            

            

                    @headers[header.strip] = i
          
      123. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    123. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      124. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    124. 
            
            

            

                }
          
      125. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    125. 
            
            

            

            
          
      126. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    126. 
            
            

            

                # examine spreadsheet headers to make sure they conform to vocabulary
          
      127. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    127. 
            
            

            

                @headers.keys.each do |ch|
          
      128. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    128. 
            
            

            

                  if !COLUMN_HEADERS.include?(ch)
          
      129. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    129. 
            
            

            

                    @parse_headers_msg << "><b>#{ch}</b>< is not a valid column header<br/>".html_safe
          
      130. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    130. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      131. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    131. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      132. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    132. 
            
            

            

                # make sure that every header is present in the spreadsheet
          
      133. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    133. 
            
            

            

                COLUMN_HEADERS.each do |h|
          
      134. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    134. 
            
            

            

                  unless @headers.keys.include?(h)
          
      135. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    135. 
            
            

            

                    @parse_headers_msg <<  "The column <b>#{h}</b> is missing from the spreadsheet<br/>".html_safe
          
      136. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    136. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      137. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    137. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      138. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    138. 
            
            

            

              end
          
      139. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    139. 
            
            

            

            
          
      140. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    140. 
            
            

            

              # this method parses a single row in the spreadsheet trying to reconstitute a physical object - it creates association objects (title, series, etc) as well
          
      141. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    141. 
            
            

            

              def parse_physical_object(row, i)
          
      142. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    142. 
            
            

            

                puts("Parsing Physical Object at Row: #{i + 1}")
          
      143. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    143. 
            
            

            

                # read all auto parse fields
          
      144. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    144. 
            
            

            

                po = RecordedSound.new(spreadsheet_id: @spreadsheet.id)
          
      145. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    145. 
            
            

            

                HEADERS_TO_ASSIGNER.keys.each do |k|
          
      146. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    146. 
            
            

            

                  po.send(HEADERS_TO_ASSIGNER[k], row[@headers[k]]) unless @headers[k].nil?
          
      147. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    147. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      148. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    148. 
            
            

            

                # date created
          
      149. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    149. 
            
            

            

                begin
          
      150. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    150. 
            
            

            

                  d = Date.strptime(row[column_index DATE_CREATED], '%Y/%m/%d')
          
      151. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    151. 
            
            

            

                  po.date_inventoried = d
          
      152. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    152. 
            
            

            

                rescue
          
      153. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    153. 
            
            

            

                  po.errors.add(:date, "Unable to parse date created")
          
      154. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    154. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      155. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    155. 
            
            

            

            
          
      156. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    156. 
            
            

            

                # manually parse the other values to ensure conformance to controlled vocabulary
          
      157. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    157. 
            
            

            

                dur = row[column_index DURATION]
          
      158. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    158. 
            
            

            

                unless dur.blank?
          
      159. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    159. 
            
            

            

                  if po.valid_duration?(dur)
          
      160. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    160. 
            
            

            

                    po.send(:duration=, dur)
          
      161. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    161. 
            
            

            

                  else
          
      162. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    162. 
            
            

            

                    po.errors.add(:duration, "Improperly formatted duration value (h:mm:ss): #{dur}")
          
      163. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    163. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      164. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    164. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      165. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    165. 
            
            

            

            
          
      166. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    166. 
            
            

            

                tc = row[column_index CAPACITY]
          
      167. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    167. 
            
            

            

                unless tc.blank?
          
      168. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    168. 
            
            

            

                    po.send(:capacity=, tc)
          
      169. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    169. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      170. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    170. 
            
            

            

            
          
      171. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    171. 
            
            

            

                # metadata fields common to all PO's
          
      172. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    172. 
            
            

            

                parse_title_control_number(po, row)
          
      173. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    173. 
            
            

            

                parse_catalog_key(po, row)
          
      174. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    174. 
            
            

            

                parse_media_type(po, row)
          
      175. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    175. 
            
            

            

                parse_po_location(po, row)
          
      176. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    176. 
            
            

            

                parse_alf_shelf_location(po, row)
          
      177. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    177. 
            
            

            

                parse_condition_rating(po, row)
          
      178. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    178. 
            
            

            

                parse_research_value(po, row)
          
      179. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    179. 
            
            

            

                parse_title_metadata(po, row)
          
      180. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    180. 
            
            

            

                parse_unit(po, row)
          
      181. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    181. 
            
            

            

                parse_user(po, row)
          
      182. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    182. 
            
            

            

                parse_accompanying_documentation(po, row)
          
      183. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    183. 
            
            

            

                # end common metadata fields
          
      184. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    184. 
            
            

            

            
          
      185. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    185. 
            
            

            

                gauge = row[column_index GAUGE]
          
      186. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    186. 
            
            

            

                if gauge.blank?

              def parse_title_control_number(po, row)
          
      371.

                # title control number

                tcn = row[column_index IUCAT_TITLE_NO]
          
      373.

              def parse_title_metadata(po, row)

                if title.title_text.blank?

                  po.errors.add(:title, "Title title text cannot be blank.")

    452. 
            
            

            

                title.spreadsheet_id = @spreadsheet.id

                title_notes = row[column_index TITLE_NOTES]

                unless title_notes.blank?

                title_subject = row[column_index SUBJECT]

      471.

      472. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    472. 
            
            

            

                dates = row[column_index DATE].to_s
          
      473. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    473. 
            
            

            

                unless dates.blank?
          
      474. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    474. 
            
            

            

                  dates.split(DELIMITER).each do |date|
          
      475. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    475. 
            
            

            

                    # the HEX codes in the middle are for MS Excel which changes '-' (minus) to en dashes and/or em dashes
          
      476. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    476. 
            
            

            

                    date_type_rgx = /^(([\[\]0-9\/\?]+)( ?[-\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x93]{1,1} ?([\[\]0-9\/\?]+))?) ?(\(([a-zA-Z ]+)\))?/
          
      477. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    477. 
            
            

            

                    match = date_type_rgx.match(date)
          
      478. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    478. 
            
            

            

                    if match.nil?
          
      479. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    479. 
            
            

            

                      po.errors.add(:title_date, "Malformed date #{date}")
          
      480. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    480. 
            
            

            

                    else
          
      481. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    481. 
            
            

            

                      begin
          
      482. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    482. 
            
            

            

                        date_set = DateHelper.convert_dates(match[1])
          
      483. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    483. 
            
            

            

                        # error case - start date will always be !nil unless the string is malformed.
          
      484. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    484. 
            
            

            

                        # DateHelper.convert_dates will also set :start_date to nil if end_date exists but is malformed
          
      485. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    485. 
            
            

            

                        if date_set[:start_date].nil?
          
      486. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    486. 
            
            

            

                          po.errors.add(:title_date, "Malformed date #{date}")
          
      487. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    487. 
            
            

            

                        else
          
      488. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    488. 
            
            

            

                          type = (match[6].blank? ? 'TBD' : @title_date_types.include?(match[6]) ? match[6] : nil)
          
      489. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    489. 
            
            

            

                          if type.nil?
          
      490. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    490. 
            
            

            

                            po.errors.add(:title_date, "Unknown title date type: #{date}")
          
      491. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    491. 
            
            

            

                          else
          
      492. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    492. 
            
            

            

                            td = TitleDate.new(title_id: title.id, date_text: match[1], date_type: type)
          
      493. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    493. 
            
            

            

                            title.title_dates << td
          
      494. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    494. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      495. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    495. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      496. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    496. 
            
            

            

                      rescue => e
          
      497. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    497. 
            
            

            

                        po.errors.add(:title_date, "Malformed date #{date}")
          
      498. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    498. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      499. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    499. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      500. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    500. 
            
            

            

                  end
          
      501. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    501. 
            
            

            

                end
          
      502. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    502. 
            
            

            

            
          
      503. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    503. 
            
            

            

                # title creators, publishers, form, genre, (subject - currently waiting on controlled vocab to implement) and location
          
      504. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    504. 
            
            

            

                creator_values = row[column_index CREATOR]
          
      505. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    505. 
            
            

            

                unless creator_values.blank?
          
      506. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    506. 
            
            

            

                  creator_values.split(DELIMITER).each do |val|
          
      507. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    507. 
            
            

            

                    matcher = NAME_ROLE_PATTERN.match(val)
          
      508.

                    if matcher

      513. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    513. 
            
            

            

                      else
          
      514.

                        po.errors.add(:title_creator, "Undefined Title Creator Role: #{role}")
          
      515. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    515.

      519.

                publisher_values = row[column_index PUBLISHER]
